Some&#3; streams&#3; of&#3; research&#3; have&#3; distinguished&#3; the&#3; types&#3; of&#3; school&#3; autonomy&#3; that&#3; seem&#3; to&#3; matter&#3; most&#3; for&#3;
influencing&#3; student&#3; learning.&#3; King&#3; and&#3; Ã–zler&#3; (2005)&#3; find&#3; that&#3; broad&#3; school&#3; autonomy&#3; in&#3; Nicaraguan&#3; public&#3; schools&#3;
has&#3;no&#3;impact&#3;on&#3;student&#3; achievement&#3; scores;&#3;however,&#3;schools&#3;with&#3;greater&#3;levels&#3;of&#3;autonomy&#3;specifically&#3;over&#3;
