the&#3;existence&#3;of&#3;private&#3;schools&#3;in&#3;Sweden&#3;led&#3;to&#3;improvements&#3;in&#3;the&#3;standards&#3;of&#3;public&#3;schools&#3;(SandstrÃ¶m&#3;and&#3;
BergstrÃ¶m&#3; 2005).&#3; De&#3; la&#3; Croix&#3; and&#3; Doepke&#3; (2009)&#3; find&#3; that,&#3; across&#3; countries,&#3; increases&#3; in&#3; private&#3; education&#3; are&#3;
associated&#3; with&#3; an&#3; improved&#3; quality&#3; of&#3; public&#3; education,&#3; as&#3; public&#3; spending&#3; is&#3; concentrated&#3; on&#3; fewer&#3; students.&#3;
Nannestad&#3;(2004)&#3;analyzed&#3;whether&#3;private&#3;schools&#3;in&#3;Denmark&#3;improved&#3;the&#3;quality&#3;of&#3;local&#3;municipal&#3;schools&#3;and&#3;
