      all&#3;Ghanaian&#3;students&#3;regardless&#3;of&#3;sector.&#3;Schools&#3;do&#3;not&#3;need&#3;to&#3;meet&#3;any&#3;particular&#3;criteria&#3;for&#3;eligibility.&#3;
      The&#3; government&#3; of&#3; Uganda&#3; subsidizes&#3; 430&#3; private&#3; secondary&#3; schools&#3; serving&#3; roughly&#3; 56,000&#3; students&#3; as&#3; a&#3;
      means&#3;to&#3;attain&#3;universal&#3;secondary&#3;education.&#3;The&#3;Ministry&#3;of&#3;Education&#3;chooses&#3;the&#3;participating&#3;schools&#3;


