    The&#3;Systems&#3;Approach&#3;for&#3;Better&#3;Education&#3;Results&#3;(SABER)&#3;initiative&#3;collects&#3;data&#3;
    on&#3; the&#3; policies&#3; and&#3; institutions&#3; of&#3; education&#3; systems&#3; around&#3; the&#3; world&#3; and&#3;
    benchmarks&#3; them&#3; against&#3; practices&#3; associated&#3; with&#3; student&#3; learning.&#3; SABER&#3; aims&#3;
    to&#3; give&#3; all&#3; parties&#3; with&#3; a&#3; stake&#3; in&#3; educational&#3; resultsâ€”from&#3; students,&#3;
    administrators,&#3; teachers,&#3; and&#3; parents&#3; to&#3; policymakers,&#3; business&#3; people&#3; and&#3;
    political&#3; leadersâ€”an&#3; accessible,&#3; detailed,&#3; objective&#3; snapshot&#3; of&#3; how&#3; well&#3; the&#3;
    policies&#3;of&#3;their&#3;countryâ€™s&#3;education&#3;system&#3;are&#3;oriented&#3;toward&#3;delivering&#3;learning&#3;
    for&#3;all&#3;children&#3;and&#3;youth.&#3;
    This&#3;framework&#3;paper&#3;focuses&#3;specifically&#3;in&#3;the&#3;area&#3;of&#3;Engaging&#3;the&#3;Private&#3;
    Sector.&#3;&#3;&#3;&#3;&#3;&#3;&#3;&#3;&#3;&#3;&#3;&#3;&#3;




